Some popular native Australian fruits include:

1. Finger Lime (Citrus australasica): Also known as caviar lime, this fruit has tiny, bead-like citrus pulp that adds a tart flavor to any dish.

2. Quandong (Santalum acuminatum): A small round red fruit with a tart and tangy taste often used in jellies, preserves or sauces.

3. Kakadu Plum (Terminalia ferdinandiana): This little green plum packs an immense amount of Vitamin C and is often eaten raw or used in jams and chutneys.

4. Desert Lime (Citrus glauca): Similar to traditional limes but smaller and more drought-tolerant, these are commonly used for their juice in marinades or dressings.

5. Muntries (Kunzea pomifera): Small berries found along the coast of South Australia have flavors reminiscent of apples and spices; they can be eaten fresh or preserved for later use.

6. Davidson's Plum (Davidsonia spp.) These plums are sour when unripe but become sweeter after being cooked â€“ widely utilized as ingredients for pastries, compotes & even wine!
